The protagonist is Bill, a hayseed from the farm who gets Shanghai into the Empire Space Corps to fight the evil Chingers.

13:11.440 --> 13:16.140
Bill, the Galactic Hero, is a spoof of war, bureaucracy, and the pulps, among other things.

13:16.620 --> 13:19.780
Here, here is some comments and some of the influences which helped inspire the novel.

13:21.020 --> 13:24.460
Bill, the Galactic Hero, there again, he was assigned the role.

13:24.600 --> 13:28.980
He was a good soldier, Shfaq.

13:29.500 --> 13:33.480
He's the guy who gets it in the neck all the time and had to be a science fiction army.

13:34.580 --> 13:37.260
And I think he just made it explode in me.

13:37.540 --> 13:43.720
Having been in the army and seated here in the heart of the military, I'm an enlisted man.

13:43.840 --> 13:45.620
I have the highest rank in the army, that of a sergeant.

13:46.040 --> 13:48.500
You have to get to general before you get anything higher than that.

13:48.540 --> 13:50.880
Second lieutenant, you know, grubs to be walked on.

13:51.520 --> 13:52.400
And the whole different attitude.

13:53.520 --> 13:55.700
And the officers like the military.

13:56.300 --> 13:58.060
They like to tell people what to do.

13:58.700 --> 14:03.560
And usually what they tell them to do is not for the good of the people they're talking to, they should get killed for it.

14:04.500 --> 14:06.640
But the enlisted men want to stay alive.

14:07.260 --> 14:11.640
As the Osirians said in Catch-22, they're trying to kill me.

14:12.040 --> 14:13.940
He didn't mean the enemy, he meant the army he was in.

14:14.780 --> 14:17.560
And knowing all this, reading all this, Catch-22 came out.

14:17.660 --> 14:19.380
I was a great fan of Kandy.

14:20.180 --> 14:31.080
And when I saw Catch-22, what he did, the heller did, he showed that there's something so awful that you have to laugh at them to understand them.

14:31.560 --> 14:34.780
If you do a military novel, you say, blood, blood, death, and testines from the trees.

14:35.140 --> 14:38.440
By the 20th time you hang the testines from the trees, you're tired of looking at them.

14:38.500 --> 14:39.700
It looks like spaghetti after a while.

14:40.660 --> 14:42.220
Repetition of horror doesn't make horror.

14:42.220 --> 14:46.080
And that's all you can do. The army is utterly horrible, boring and wasteful.

14:46.220 --> 14:47.860
The military life is boring and wasteful.

14:50.720 --> 14:54.660
And in there, I parodied a few other novels just for fun of it.

14:55.000 --> 14:59.920
But the thing that goes right through it is understanding the military.

15:01.540 --> 15:08.600
Usually I discovered that I had a Korean war veteran come up to me and come at my reunion and wouldn't have his face all shut away.

15:10.500 --> 15:14.660
And he said, you wrote Bill a Glatine Hero?

15:14.820 --> 15:16.560
I said, yes, looking for a chair to hide behind.

15:17.320 --> 15:22.260
He said, I've got a copy of every edition of that book. I carry it through to combat, you know?

15:22.720 --> 15:24.220
And that tells a story.

15:25.100 --> 15:28.300
Another guy with the same thing, John Paul.

15:28.540 --> 15:31.700
He's a real Green Beret, a kind of hitter, bangler.

15:31.740 --> 15:34.120
He worked with the Montagniers, not like John Wayne with the fake one.

15:34.200 --> 15:36.380
You know, he was up there and he killed him.

15:36.380 --> 15:36.960
He was a great killer.

15:40.600 --> 15:43.700
And Napoleon's troops carried a marshals back on their pack.

15:43.860 --> 15:46.420
He carried a copy of Bill a Glatine Hero, all through the Korean war up there.

15:47.000 --> 15:48.260
He was killing gooks and everything.

15:49.080 --> 15:51.140
And he said, his rookie's in.

15:51.480 --> 15:54.500
He reads him a chapter every night whether they liked it or not.

15:54.880 --> 15:56.100
He'd break him in half, you know?

15:56.900 --> 16:01.240
So I really feel that it's humor and parody and a lot of fun.

16:01.240 --> 16:05.920
But it tells you something about the military condition that is absolutely dead true.

16:11.700 --> 16:16.480
In fact, Harrison believes his version of war, as depicted in Bill the Galactic Hero,

16:16.980 --> 16:20.080
comes closer to reality than do the more serious novels of others.

16:20.760 --> 16:25.280
The pro-military novel is like Starship Trooper, you know, where everyone's being kind to each other.

16:25.280 --> 16:29.560
I mean, in fact, I saw Norman Spindrad put it in the article the other week.

16:30.840 --> 16:33.900
As Harry Harrison said, Bill Glatine, it's always Bob your buddy week.

16:34.680 --> 16:39.080
