rather than simply telling the reader the situation directly.

20:46.680 --> 20:48.940
I think having worked as an artist for a number of years,

20:49.560 --> 20:52.240
I see in my mind, and I'm writing, I have a stage of people walking around,

20:52.380 --> 20:53.800
and I see what's in the background, the foreground,

20:54.060 --> 20:55.780
I hear the waves splashing and see them splashing.

20:58.800 --> 21:04.660
And as always in writing, you should never tell you should show.

21:06.580 --> 21:08.120
And Good Rang is hard work.

21:08.540 --> 21:09.480
It should be transparent.

21:10.260 --> 21:12.360
The reader should not see how you got the effect.

21:12.900 --> 21:14.820
And one of the best ways, of course, it's hard to do,

21:14.960 --> 21:17.620
is never say the world is full of a lot of people,

21:18.080 --> 21:19.500
never say you're short of water, show them,

21:20.440 --> 21:22.460
unaligned to get water out of a standpipe.

21:22.460 --> 21:26.280
And then you know you're short of water and dramatize their need for the water.

21:27.140 --> 21:33.160
And this is where your art comes in, which far too often,

21:33.260 --> 21:37.600
if the writer cannot do that, then he does not succeed on that level.

21:37.820 --> 21:39.140
People read his book for fun, you know.

21:39.560 --> 21:41.160
But if you can get the reader emotionally involved,

21:41.740 --> 21:42.960
get him trapped into the book,

21:43.300 --> 21:46.300
and he comes out of the end, maybe not agreeing with you,

21:46.400 --> 21:48.760
but at least he knows what you're said, he'll be thinking about it.

21:49.100 --> 21:51.100
And I had one girl read that book out in New York.

21:51.100 --> 21:53.260
She said, if I thought the world would be like that, I commit suicide.

21:53.260 --> 21:54.380
I said, don't, don't.

21:55.120 --> 21:57.160
The actor thinking that means you're going to vote right

21:57.160 --> 21:59.740
and work for this world will not appeal.

22:00.180 --> 22:02.160
That's a science fiction admonishing finger again,

22:02.400 --> 22:03.780
saying shape up or ship out.

22:04.140 --> 22:05.280
If you don't do this, you'll get that.

22:06.440 --> 22:08.600
Make Room, Make Room is also a mystery novel.

22:09.040 --> 22:13.160
Harrison shows this vehicle because it allowed him to show society from bottom to top.

22:13.780 --> 22:17.320
All of science fiction, for the most part, is based on detective plot.

22:17.860 --> 22:19.160
The mystery, will it be solved?

22:19.780 --> 22:23.420
Even if they're not called like Hell, Clemens, Needle, not officially a mystery,

22:24.100 --> 22:25.460
you want to find out how you got that way?

22:25.560 --> 22:28.040
Will they solve the problem? Will they all live? Will they get all this world?

22:28.360 --> 22:29.000
Will they do it?

22:29.340 --> 22:33.600
That was the deliberate bit of my plot, a plot device of mine

22:33.600 --> 22:37.460
that I wanted to show society from the lowest level to the high.

22:37.880 --> 22:39.660
I wanted to show how everybody lived in that world.

22:40.100 --> 22:42.680
So I used a very simple device of having a detective as a protagonist.

22:43.480 --> 22:44.340
A very simple story.

22:44.800 --> 22:46.560
And we all know from the beginning who did the murder.

22:46.560 --> 22:48.300
We knew what was going to happen.

22:49.100 --> 22:51.960
And it was not important, but it was a device to move the story along.

22:52.340 --> 22:55.120
And like most crimes in New York, 9% aren't solved.

22:55.640 --> 22:57.000
Just by chance that they are.

22:57.380 --> 23:00.260
This is a way of getting you into the various levels of the strategy of society.

